Implementation of Parnas' solution to the cigarette smoker's problem in C++.
For information on the problem: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cigarette_smokers_problem

Compiling:
From a linux terminal, use the command 'g++ -o smoke cig_smoker.cpp -lpthread'
Note: '-lpthread' is used in the linking stage to find pthread.h symbols

Running:
From a linux terminal, use the command './smoke' to run the executable